name: Test -> control module 1 (cube_ctrl1),
description: Test continuity across control module 1 (cube_ctrl1) with the switch ON to determine if the module is providing a closed path (0 ohm or near-zero resistance) between input and output terminals., outcome='Continuity test results show a short (closed path) between Control Input Cable (+) 1 and Control Output Cable (+) 1 (0.11 Ω), and between Control Input Cable (−) 1 and Control Output Cable (−) 1 (0.10 Ω). No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=60.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module 2 (cube_ctrl2),
description: Test continuity across control module 2 (cube_ctrl2) with the switch ON to verify that it also provides a closed path, similar to control module 1., outcome='Continuity measurements for all cables associated with Control Module 2 are nominal, with measured resistance matching the expected value of 0.10 Ω. No polarity inversion is detected. Switch 2 was already closed prior to testing.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=90.0, cost_breakdown=[('close_switch', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module 3 (cube_ctrl3),
description: Test continuity across control module 3 (cube_ctrl3) with the switch ON, to verify that it is providing a closed (low resistance) path and to check for possible open circuit or high-resistance fault., outcome="All measured resistances across the cables and switch are nominal, indicating proper continuity when the switch is ON. However, an anomaly was detected: the 'Control Input Cable (+) 3' has a disconnected end at port 'n', which is currently floating and was originally connected to 'Control Switch 3'. No polarity inversion was observed.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=120.0, cost_breakdown=[('close_switch', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
